parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The absence of a shut-off valve near the generator set (GENSET) can cause a serious potential for massive fire and explosion when the GENSET is removed for repairs, as the fuel in the supply line cannot be evacuated.
symptoms: The GENSET will not start and run to consume the fuel in the supply line
causing a large cloud of propane gas to be released when the GENSET is removed for repairs.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The restriction in the gas fuel line can cause the fuel pump to shut off prematurely, resulting in incomplete fueling, and potentially leading to gas spills and safety hazards.
symptoms: The fuel pump stops at about 3/4 tank capacity
requiring continuous re-clicking of the pump to complete filling
sometimes leading to gas running out on the ground.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden failure of the tire sidewall can cause loss of control, accidents, and damage to the vehicle, potentially leading to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: and molding around the tire broken and loose.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electrical System Failure Leading to Fire
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause fires, which can lead to serious damage to the vehicle, injury, or even death.
symptoms: loss of power to accessories such as air conditioner

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power switch box can cause electrical fires, which can lead to serious damage to the vehicle, injury, or even death.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Manufacturer's Lack of Accountability for Third-Party Parts
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The lack of accountability by the manufacturer for third-party parts can lead to financial losses for the consumer, as they may be required to pay for repairs or replacements out of pocket.
symptoms: lack of support for defective parts installed by the manufacturer.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the automatic emergency parking brake can cause the vehicle to roll forward or backward when in park, potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle rolls forward or backward when in park
the parking brake does not hold
the brake shoes wear out prematurely.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Cable Failure due to Proximity to Exhaust System
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake cable due to its proximity to the exhaust system can cause the brake shoes to burn out and fail, leading to a loss of braking power and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: The brake shoes wear out prematurely
the brake cable fails to release the brake shoes
the brakes do not function properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The close proximity of the brake and gas pedals can cause accidental acceleration when attempting to brake, potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The foot hits the gas pedal when attempting to brake
